# MMO001 Workflow

## Before implementation

1. Read [TODO.md](../../TODO.md) and identify the **next unchecked item**
2. Summarize scope and approach before coding (plan mode or brief outline)
3. Mark the item in progress; do not start unrelated work

## Git branches

- One feature per branch from `main`: `feature/<short-kebab-name>`
- Examples: `feature/click-to-move`, `feature/mouse-aim`, `feature/monster-combat`
- Merge to `main` only when the feature is complete and smoke-tested
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials)

## Versioning (each merged feature)

1. Bump `version` in [package.json](../../package.json) (semver: patch/minor by scope)
2. Move [CHANGELOG.md](../../CHANGELOG.md) `[Unreleased]` entries into a dated version section
3. Update [README.md](../../README.md) if behavior, setup, or controls changed
4. Check off the completed item in [TODO.md](../../TODO.md)

## Commit messages

- Imperative mood, 1–2 sentences focusing on **why**
- Example: `Add click-to-move with A* pathfinding`

## Module layout

- `server/` — backend logic only
- `public/js/` — client rendering, input, UI
- `shared/` — constants, events, algorithms used by both sides
- New systems go in focused modules; avoid monolithic files
